text.p: These are some of the leading stories in the Jordanian press on Tuesday. Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.
- King leaves for U.S.; priority to put peace process back on track.
- Crown Prince Hassan: Jordan's role in Jerusalem shrines is a religious, historic duty. "Holy City represents the spiritual dimension of Arab-Israeli struggle".
- Jordan lodges strong formal protest against Israeli bid to "impose sovereignty on Arab East Jerusalem".
- Jordan strongly protests Israeli measures in Jerusalem.
- Royal decree issued postponing parliament's regular session to November 19.
- Plans underway to set up "land fund" to organise investment in state-owned lands on commercial basis.
- Prince Hassan receives Australian cultural minister and reviews bilateral ties.
- Prime Minister Abdul-Karim al-Kabariti stresses need for Israel to respect Jordan's supervisory role over holy Moslem shrines.
- Jordan's information minister says there was no agreement with Israel and the PLO to open tunnel (in Jerusalem).
